03:32.345 --> 03:34.247
Oh.

04:09.116 --> 04:10.617
Fuck.

04:10.617 --> 04:13.286
What the fuck?

04:16.690 --> 04:18.291
Oh, shit.

05:18.251 --> 05:20.453
I thought you said that
you were considering it.

05:20.453 --> 05:21.988
I did.

05:21.988 --> 05:23.757
I thought long and hard about it.

05:23.757 --> 05:26.526
It just...

05:26.526 --> 05:30.197
I don't know, it just didn't
feel right to me anymore.

05:30.197 --> 05:32.299
And so you wanna go
with this ending instead?

05:32.299 --> 05:34.467
I think it's really powerful.

05:34.467 --> 05:36.136
Well, what can I tell you?

05:36.136 --> 05:37.103
I don't agree.

05:37.103 --> 05:38.705
Oh, come on, Harry.

05:38.705 --> 05:40.307
It's much subtler.

05:40.307 --> 05:42.342
It's two people sitting down to dinner.

05:42.342 --> 05:44.344
Yeah, with an unimaginable
secret between them.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.080
Doesn't have the punch of your first idea.

05:47.080 --> 05:49.115
Murder, it's... it's...

05:49.115 --> 05:50.350
it's salacious.

05:50.350 --> 05:51.551
It's... it's cheap. It...

05:51.551 --> 05:53.753
Well, it doesn't have to be.

05:53.753 --> 05:57.324
Have you read Of Mice and Men?

05:57.324 --> 05:58.658
Is that a rhetorical question?

05:58.658 --> 06:00.427
Well, you may want to review it.

06:00.427 --> 06:03.096
The murder at the end of
that book felt surprising

06:03.096 --> 06:04.464
while it was happening

06:04.464 --> 06:08.335
and completely inevitable in retrospect.

06:08.335 --> 06:12.272
Like all great endings in literature.

06:12.272 --> 06:14.007
So what are you saying,

06:14.007 --> 06:16.710
you won't publish it if
I don't change the ending?

06:16.710 --> 06:18.545
I'm not saying that.

06:18.545 --> 06:20.447
'Cause, you know, as generous
as that advance you got me was,

06:20.447 --> 06:22.249
I still only got a fifth of it.

06:22.249 --> 06:24.517
That's because that's how advances work.

06:24.517 --> 06:27.721
You'll get the next part when
you submit the final draft.

06:27.721 --> 06:30.190
This is the final draft.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.094
Maybe you should take
another pass at the end.

06:34.094 --> 06:35.629
No, just one more pass.

06:35.629 --> 06:37.397
Oh, God.

06:39.266 --> 06:41.134
Okay, maybe I should be more articulate

06:41.134 --> 06:43.670
about what I did appreciate in this draft.

06:43.670 --> 06:45.505
I thought bringing the feud

06:45.505 --> 06:48.008
to the foreground of the earlier chapters

06:48.008 --> 06:49.376
worked beautifully.

06:49.376 --> 06:52.512
There's something almost epic in the way

06:52.512 --> 06:54.014
that you now depict that
family, those four brothers...

06:54.014 --> 06:55.548
"Almost"?

06:55.548 --> 06:57.384
It's got a real East of Eden feel to me.

06:57.384 --> 06:59.052
What is it with you and Steinbeck today?

06:59.052 --> 07:03.256
And I love the way that
you introduced Lana.

07:03.256 --> 07:04.724
And I gotta ask, how much of this is

07:04.724 --> 07:08.295
based on what happened between you and, um,

07:08.295 --> 07:09.696
what's her actual name?

07:09.696 --> 07:12.666
It's fiction, Harry.

07:12.666 --> 07:16.269
All right. All right.

07:17.704 --> 07:21.207
I know this is frustrating for you,

07:21.207 --> 07:23.243
but you're in the final stretch, buddy.

07:23.243 --> 07:25.512
Don't go soft on me, okay?

07:25.512 --> 07:27.614
You have something very powerful to say.

07:27.614 --> 07:31.284
I just want you to say it.

07:45.065 --> 07:47.067
- Noah!
- Hey, Jordy.

07:47.067 --> 07:48.702
- How's it going?
- Man, it's been forever.

07:48.702 --> 07:50.136
Where you been?

07:50.136 --> 07:52.105
Uh, I... I've been upstate,

07:52.105 --> 07:54.307
in a little... just a writer's retreat.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.242
Working on something new or...

07:56.242 --> 07:57.544
- That's right, yeah.
- I can't wait to read it.

07:57.544 --> 07:59.179
You know, I feel terrible

07:59.179 --> 08:00.313
we haven't seen more
of you guys this summer.

08:00.313 --> 08:01.748
We've been meaning to have you over.

08:01.748 --> 08:03.183
It's just with the end of the school year,

08:03.183 --> 08:04.317
you know how it is.

08:04.317 --> 08:05.752
Everything's so out of control.

08:05.752 --> 08:07.187
And Becca's mother is
staying with us right now,

08:07.187 --> 08:08.588
which makes me wanna...

08:08.588 --> 08:10.523
What are you doing tonight?

08:10.523 --> 08:12.559
Um, I... Oh, I...

08:12.559 --> 08:13.994
No, fuck, I can't tonight.

08:13.994 --> 08:15.428
- Daddy.
- Duck.

08:15.428 --> 08:16.696
I said "duck."

08:16.696 --> 08:18.231
Uh, listen, as soon as I get home,

08:18.231 --> 08:19.766
I'm gonna check the Google Calendar

08:19.766 --> 08:21.334
and have Becca call Helen and make a date.

08:21.334 --> 08:23.436
- How's that sound?
- Great.

08:23.436 --> 08:24.704
It's great to see you, man. You look good.

08:24.704 --> 08:26.373
You too.

08:44.691 --> 08:47.627
Hey, I'm Noah Solloway. Sorry I'm late.

08:47.627 --> 08:50.063
No problem, dude. We're ready to go.

08:50.063 --> 08:52.432
How much stuff you got?

08:54.467 --> 08:56.603
You know what, this is a
kind of sensitive situation.

08:56.603 --> 08:59.472
You just wait here.
I'll bring the stuff out.

08:59.472 --> 09:00.640
All of it?

09:00.640 --> 09:03.643
Yeah, yeah. I think I can manage.

09:03.643 --> 09:05.578
All right, man. Whatever works.

09:27.233 --> 09:28.234
Where's Helen?

09:28.234 --> 09:30.036
She's not here.

09:30.036 --> 09:32.005
Where did she go?

09:32.005 --> 09:35.108
That's none of your business.

09:35.108 --> 09:36.342
Okay, I'm here to...

09:36.342 --> 09:38.178
I know why you're here.

09:38.178 --> 09:40.580
That's why I'm here.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.415
Oh.

09:43.983 --> 09:45.118
Can I...

09:45.118 --> 09:47.420
Oh, by all means, come in.

09:52.025 --> 09:53.259
Kids?

09:53.259 --> 09:56.062
I've sent them all away.

09:56.062 --> 09:57.130
You sent them away?

09:57.130 --> 09:58.698
Yes, Noah.

09:58.698 --> 10:00.500
I didn't think it would do them any favors

10:00.500 --> 10:02.969
to be subjected to the
traumatic consequences

10:02.969 --> 10:05.138
of their father's psychosis.

10:05.138 --> 10:06.739
Helen and I have taken the liberty

10:06.739 --> 10:08.241
of putting most of your things

10:08.241 --> 10:10.710
in the basement.

10:16.349 --> 10:18.418
Thanks.

10:33.533 --> 10:35.268
Where's the rest of my stuff, Margaret?

10:35.268 --> 10:36.703
It hasn't been appraised.

10:36.703 --> 10:37.704
What?

10:37.704 --> 10:39.539
Once the divorce is finalized,

10:39.539 --> 10:42.342
we'll have a professional
make an inventory of the house

10:42.342 --> 10:44.444
and determine the value of
the rest of the property,

10:44.444 --> 10:46.613
and then we'll ship you
whatever you're owed,

10:46.613 --> 10:49.449
or Helen can just write a check.

10:49.449 --> 10:51.151
Since, let's just be honest,

10:51.151 --> 10:53.586
what you really need is money, isn't it?

11:04.297 --> 11:06.599
Is this all your stuff?

11:09.202 --> 11:11.137
No, it's not.

11:15.441 --> 11:17.410
What do you think you're doing?

11:17.410 --> 11:20.079
These books are mine. I'm taking them.

11:20.079 --> 11:21.748
Not until their value has been determined.

11:21.748 --> 11:23.483
They're paperbacks!

11:23.483 --> 11:26.052
They might have sentimental value to Helen.

11:26.052 --> 11:27.487
Put that back! That's Le Creuset!

11:27.487 --> 11:29.622
Noah, I'm not gonna ask you again.

11:29.622 --> 11:31.291
Margaret, be reasonable.

11:31.291 --> 11:33.092
These mugs are chipped.
This pot is stained.

11:33.092 --> 11:36.095
I don't care if they have
holes in the goddamn bottom!

11:36.095 --> 11:37.630
Noah, get back here!

11:37.630 --> 11:39.599
Who do you think you are?

11:39.599 --> 11:43.269
This is my daughter's
house! This is her property!

11:43.269 --> 11:44.971
And the fact that you had the audacity

11:44.971 --> 11:46.439
to come and show your face here

11:46.439 --> 11:48.174
after what you've done to my family...

11:48.174 --> 11:50.677
Absolutely not! It has to be appraised!

11:50.677 --> 11:52.512
I swear, if you don't
stop what you're doing,

11:52.512 --> 11:54.113
I'm gonna call the police.

11:54.113 --> 11:56.115
Margaret, my father painted
this fucking painting.

11:56.115 --> 11:57.350
Now if you don't get out of my way,

11:57.350 --> 11:58.618
I swear to God I'll push you down

11:58.618 --> 12:00.186
the fucking flight of stairs behind you,

12:00.186 --> 12:02.288
and I'll tell the coroner
it was a fucking accident!

12:02.288 --> 12:04.524
Dad?

12:06.459 --> 12:09.329
Hey, buddy.

12:09.329 --> 12:11.531
I thought you weren't here.

12:14.000 --> 12:14.968
Oops.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.641
Can I come in?

12:29.515 --> 12:31.284
How you doing?

12:31.284 --> 12:34.454
Stomachache.

12:34.454 --> 12:36.189
What kind of stomachache?

12:36.189 --> 12:38.691
The kind that hurts.

12:38.691 --> 12:41.227
Think you're getting sick?

12:41.227 --> 12:44.063
I'll be fine, Dad. Just leave me alone.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.670
Well, I hope you get better soon.

12:50.670 --> 12:53.172
I got tickets for the Yankees tomorrow.

12:53.172 --> 12:55.975
Spend the whole day together.

12:55.975 --> 12:59.279
Talk about what's been going
on between your mom and me,

12:59.279 --> 13:00.713
just the two of us.

13:00.713 --> 13:01.748
I can't go.

13:01.748 --> 13:04.284
What do you mean you can't go?

13:04.284 --> 13:06.386
I have a psychologist appointment.

13:06.386 --> 13:09.055
You have what?

13:09.055 --> 13:11.057
Grandma made it for me.

13:14.060 --> 13:16.562
He's the best adolescent
psychologist in the city.

13:16.562 --> 13:18.331
I had to use every bit of influence I had

13:18.331 --> 13:20.066
to make this appointment.

13:20.066 --> 13:21.668
Noah, your son hasn't been
out of his room in a month.

13:21.668 --> 13:23.536
I watched him play basketball last week!

13:23.536 --> 13:25.371
We are all incredibly worried about him.

13:25.371 --> 13:27.707
His stomachaches seem to be getting worse,

13:27.707 --> 13:30.310
especially when you come around.

13:32.745 --> 13:34.580
Margaret, I gotta ask you,

13:34.580 --> 13:37.050
how the fuck do you face yourself

13:37.050 --> 13:39.319
in the mirror each morning?

13:39.319 --> 13:41.220
How the fuck do you?

13:45.625 --> 13:47.193
Listen, I can't be there to meet you.

13:47.193 --> 13:49.028
I gotta take care of something in the city,

13:49.028 --> 13:51.497
but, uh, just leave it all
on the deck outside, okay?

13:51.497 --> 13:54.233
Absolutely, man. You're the boss.

13:58.171 --> 14:00.506
Here you go.

14:09.315 --> 14:11.217
Dad?

14:11.217 --> 14:15.188
- Hi, Dad!
- Trevor, hey!

14:15.188 --> 14:17.990
Where have you been? I
thought you were at camp.

14:17.990 --> 14:19.726
I hate camp. It's too sporty.

14:19.726 --> 14:21.627
But it's theater camp, isn't it?

14:21.627 --> 14:23.996
Yeah, but it's outdoors in the park,

14:23.996 --> 14:25.998
and they want to do all
these movement games.

14:25.998 --> 14:28.234
And, like, three kids
have already gotten ticks.

14:28.234 --> 14:29.602
Did you run away?

14:29.602 --> 14:31.137
It's fine. I left a note.

14:31.137 --> 14:32.705
Let's go to the movies.

14:32.705 --> 14:34.474
Come on, Trevor, Trevor,
we have to go back to camp.

14:34.474 --> 14:36.109
But why? Why can't we hang out?

14:36.109 --> 14:38.378
I can't. I'm on my way to an appointment.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.313
What kind of appointment?

14:40.313 --> 14:42.382
I'm meeting... meeting with your mom.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.183
I knew you'd work it out. I knew it.

14:44.183 --> 14:45.651
Whitney said you were getting divorced,

14:45.651 --> 14:48.654
but I told her no, that was ridiculous.

14:50.590 --> 14:53.393
Okay, let's... let's, um...

14:53.393 --> 14:55.261
just sit down on the stoop
for a minute, come here.

14:55.261 --> 14:57.163
Why?

14:57.163 --> 14:59.599
Just... just sit down.

15:01.267 --> 15:02.668
So what has... what has Mom said

15:02.668 --> 15:04.570
about what's happening between her and me?

15:04.570 --> 15:08.374
She said you're having a midlife crisis.

15:08.374 --> 15:09.675
She did?

15:09.675 --> 15:11.210
Yeah, and she said you need some time

15:11.210 --> 15:12.979
to get your head out of your ass,

15:12.979 --> 15:15.415
and then you'll be back
and everything will be fine.

15:17.683 --> 15:19.419
Okay, listen, little man.

15:19.419 --> 15:21.754
Listen to me.

15:21.754 --> 15:25.158
I have to tell you something,
and it's gonna suck, okay?

15:25.158 --> 15:28.027
Your mom and I, we are getting a divorce.

15:29.128 --> 15:30.563
No.

15:30.563 --> 15:32.031
Yeah.

15:34.734 --> 15:37.136
I'm sorry.

15:37.136 --> 15:38.337
I'm sorry, buddy.

15:38.337 --> 15:40.473
I know that's not what you wanna hear.

15:40.473 --> 15:43.109
Why?

15:43.109 --> 15:45.411
It's... it's very complicated.

15:45.411 --> 15:46.679
What did Mom do?

15:46.679 --> 15:48.414
She didn't do anything.

15:48.414 --> 15:50.016
Then why are you divorcing her?

15:50.016 --> 15:53.553
Because we don't get along so well anymore,

15:53.553 --> 15:57.623
and because I...

15:57.623 --> 16:01.627
I fell in love with somebody else.

16:01.627 --> 16:03.229
How?

16:05.598 --> 16:08.034
I don't know exactly. I just did.

16:10.403 --> 16:13.306
But you're married to Mom.

16:13.306 --> 16:16.309
Look, sometimes...

16:16.309 --> 16:18.077
sometimes you can fall
in love with somebody

16:18.077 --> 16:20.179
you're not married to.

16:20.179 --> 16:22.715
And sometimes the way you love
the person you are married to,

16:22.715 --> 16:26.686
it can... it can change.

16:26.686 --> 16:28.521
Can the way you love
your children change too?

16:28.521 --> 16:30.590
No, no, not at all.

16:30.590 --> 16:33.459
That always stays exactly the same.

16:36.128 --> 16:37.997
Look, I know this doesn't
make a lot of sense to you now,

16:37.997 --> 16:40.333
but I promise you one
day you'll understand.

16:40.333 --> 16:43.236
I promise, okay? And
it's not gonna be so bad.

16:43.236 --> 16:44.604
I'm gonna get a new place,

16:44.604 --> 16:46.239
and you're gonna have your own room.

16:46.239 --> 16:47.340
I don't want a new room!

16:47.340 --> 16:49.242
Trevor... Oh, fuck!

16:49.242 --> 16:51.744
Ow. Trevor, come...

16:51.744 --> 16:55.214
Trevor, come back!

16:55.214 --> 16:57.483
Ow!

16:57.483 --> 16:59.151
Oh, shit.

17:00.620 --> 17:03.022
Ow.

17:05.491 --> 17:07.760
Oh, fuck.

17:12.298 --> 17:14.967
Hi, sorry I'm late.

17:14.967 --> 17:16.202
What happened?

17:16.202 --> 17:17.303
Oh, it's nothing.

17:17.303 --> 17:18.471
Don't worry about it.

17:18.471 --> 17:20.071
Who's worried?

17:20.071 --> 17:22.308
Mr. Solloway. Jeremy.

17:22.308 --> 17:24.377
Welcome. Have a seat.

17:30.650 --> 17:32.118
Are you okay?

17:33.519 --> 17:35.488
I'm fine.

17:35.488 --> 17:37.690
So since we're already short on time,

